Job Title: Mechatronics Engineer (1-Year Fixed Term) - Mount Waverley
Ad Text:
Enjoy a dynamic role where every day is different.

1-Year Fixed-Term Contract with the potential to access future global career pathways across Danaher's world-class brands.

Work in a fast-paced global organisation dedicated to advancing cancer diagnostics and improving patient outcomes.

Join a large, supportive, cross-functional R&D team that values collaboration and continuous learning.

Gain end-to-end exposure to the full product design lifecycle—from concept development through testing and transfer to manufacturing.

Perfect for detail-oriented engineers who thrive in technical documentation, design change processes, and structured engineering environments.

Work-life balance with a 9–5 schedule and flexible start and finish times.




Bring more to life.
Are you ready to accelerate your potential and make a real difference within life sciences, diagnostics and biotechnology?

At Leica Biosystems, one of Danaher’s 15+ operating companies, our work saves lives—and we’re all united by a shared commitment to innovate for tangible impact.

You’ll thrive in a culture of belonging where you and your unique viewpoint matter. And by harnessing Danaher’s system of continuous improvement, you help turn ideas into impact – innovating at the speed of life.

At Leica Biosystems, we’re not just shaping the future of cancer diagnostics — we’re transforming lives. Our mission of “Advancing Cancer Diagnostics, Improving Lives” is the driving force behind everything we do. As a global leader with the most comprehensive portfolio spanning from biopsy to diagnosis, we empower clinicians with innovative, reliable solutions so they can give patients timely, accurate answers when they need them most. When you join Leica Biosystems, you’re not just taking a job; you’re becoming part of a passionate team that knows every moment matters when it comes to cancer. You’ll help develop diagnostic solutions that turn anxiety into answers, and aid the acceleration of next-generation, life-changing therapies. Surrounded by a diverse and collaborative global community, you’ll be inspired each day to stretch, grow, and make an impact.

Learn about the Danaher Business System which makes everything possible.

The Mechatronics Engineer will play a key role in delivering innovative solutions within a collaborative project delivery team structure. This position is responsible for problem solving, designing, testing, and implementing mechanical and mechatronic engineering solutions, ensuring all technical documentation is completed accurately and on time. The role applies advanced engineering principles to support product development and project execution from concept through delivery.

Location: This 1-year fixed term position reports to the Hardware Engineering Manager and is part of the R&D department located in Mount Waverley, Melbourne and will be an on-site role.

In this role, you will have the opportunity to:

Conduct design activities independently that include but are not limited to: Robotics, Mechanisms, Structures, System analysis, Fluidics and Thermal systems, while following R&D standard work processes such as planning, documentation and visual management activities.

Applying engineering methods and manufacturing process requirements to design components, mechanisms, and assemblies in the context of reliability improvements, VAVE, compliance requirements (e.g. RoHS), obsolescence or new product development.

Support in root cause analysis and solving technical problems with instruments in production or in the field.

Prototype building including design, construction and programming to run functional and verification testing of products.

Provide support to the rest of the business in response to requests for assistance in matters relating to engineering issues

The essential requirements of the job include:

Degree qualified in Mechatronics Engineering or equivalent

Good understanding in hybrid mechanical, electronic and software systems comprising of sensors, microcontrollers, motors, heating/cooling systems, pneumatics, fluidics

Hands on experience in prototype building cycle including design, construction, and programming to run functional and verification testing of products, ideally within fast-paced highly regulated industries (medical devices, aerospace, defense, pharmaceuticals).

Capable to establish detailed actions plan based on high level milestones and work autonomously to drive to completion.

Positive, self-motivated disposition and personal accountability.

Manager, AI Strategy & Delivery




Newly created role

Sydney - Hybrid

Exclusive to Interface Agency

We have been engaged by a major Australian organisation undertaking a significant uplift in digital, data and AI capability. With strong executive sponsorship and substantial enterprise-wide commitment, this organisation is poised for a major transformation in how it leverages AI to drive performance, safety, efficiency and innovation.

To support this next horizon of growth, we are seeking an exceptional Manager, AI Strategy & Delivery to shape, govern and drive the enterprise AI agenda.

This is a career-defining opportunity to stand up and own AI strategy at scale — ensuring AI is safe, explainable, commercially impactful and embedded across the business.

The Opportunity

Reporting to a senior digital leader, you will lead the development, execution and governance of the organisation’s AI roadmap. Your remit spans strategy, delivery, guardrails, adoption, literacy and benefits realisation.

You’ll play a pivotal role in identifying high-value AI opportunities, embedding Responsible AI practices, and uplifting organisational readiness — ensuring the organisation benefits meaningfully from both classical ML and emerging GenAI capabilities.

This is a role for an AI leader who can confidently move between board-level strategy, enterprise governance, and hands-on delivery leadership.

Key Responsibilities

In this role, you will:

Define and evolve the enterprise AI roadmap, ensuring alignment to strategic priorities and measurable business value.

Identify and evaluate AI opportunities across business units, maximising value from emerging technologies.

Establish and chair AI governance forums, setting standards for model risk, evaluation, approval processes and Responsible AI.

Lead delivery of priority AI services — including GenAI assistants and ML models — partnering closely with Data Science, Digital Innovation and engineering squads.

Develop and enforce MLOps standards (feature stores, CI/CD, observability, rollback, registries).

Lead AI literacy uplift through training pathways, communities of practice, enablement playbooks and safe-use guidance.

Embed Responsible AI controls (privacy, fairness, safety, transparency) in partnership with Legal, Risk and Data Governance.

Ensure certified datasets, semantic models, lineage management and data quality underpin all AI development.

Oversee commercial relationships with cloud providers, AI vendors and delivery partners; optimise cost, value and outcomes.

Report progress, risks, adoption and value realisation to senior leadership through structured insights and dashboards.

Champion reuse of prompts, features, evaluation suites and shared patterns to accelerate time-to-value and improve quality.

Key Challenges

To thrive, you'll be comfortable navigating:

Balancing rapid experimentation with Responsible AI guardrails and regulatory expectations.

Driving organisational change across stakeholders with varying levels of AI maturity.

Ensuring enterprise data readiness — quality, lineage, access — to support scalable AI.

Preventing tool and vendor fragmentation in a complex landscape.

Competing for scarce AI/ML talent in a fast-moving market.

Key Relationships

You will partner closely with:
Internal: Data Governance, Data Science & Engineering, Digital Innovation, Senior Leaders, Board-level committees.
External: Cloud providers, AI vendors, delivery partners, and relevant regulatory or industry bodies.

About You

You will bring a blend of strategic leadership, delivery discipline and deep domain expertise, including:

7+ years in applied AI/ML, with at least 3 years leading cross-functional delivery across both GenAI and classical ML.

Strong hands-on familiarity with MLOps practices and modern data platforms on Azure, AWS or GCP.

A proven ability to influence executive stakeholders and translate technical concepts into business-aligned decisions.

Experience designing and enforcing AI guardrails, ensuring safety, fairness, explainability and compliance.

Demonstrated success in organisational enablement — scaling literacy, communities of practice and enterprise adoption.

Strong vendor management capability and experience optimising commercial outcomes.

Tertiary qualifications in Computer Science, Data Science, Engineering or a related field.

Why This Role Is Exceptional

Enterprise scale: Drive AI uplift across a large, complex organisation.

Executive backing: Strong sponsorship ensures traction, investment and visibility.

Impact: Shape AI capability that will materially influence organisational performance, safety and customer outcomes.

Breadth: Strategy, governance, delivery, adoption and culture — all yours to lead.

Timing: Join at the foundational phase, where your direction sets the blueprint for years to come.

Apply Now! We are moving quickly!!

Job Description

The Team

The AI & Analytics Data Products team builds high-quality data assets that empower teams across SEEK Group to gain valuable insights and enhance experiences for both individuals and organisations.

This position will report to the Engineering Manager and be part of a team made up of senior and mid-level data engineers. The team collaborates closely with internal peers, including staff, senior, and mid-level data engineers; analytics engineers; data solution designers; and data tracking specialists.

About the role 

A Lead Data Engineer is a hands-on technical role, contributing to the build and operation of technical solutions, but has additional leadership responsibility for people management and delivery outcomes.

Responsibilities 

Technology

Hands-on development and operational support duties alongside other data engineers.
Ongoing ownership of solutions you build to ensure they remain fit for purpose, meet customer needs, meet technology health metrics, and align with architectural guidelines.

Delivery

Driving customer focus and engagement to ensure we are delivering outcomes for our customers.
Setting goals, prioritising, planning, as well as contributing to budgeting and resourcing
Lead delivery and operation of data products, along with the data processing pipelines and orchestration to deliver them.

People

Direct line management of a small team of engineers
Performance review and management of individuals.
Professional growth via coaching and mentoring.
Qualifications

Skills and experience 

Proven years of experience in Data Engineering, delivering scalable, reliable, and production-grade data solutions on cloud platforms
Deep expertise in big data processing frameworks, ideally Apache Spark on Databricks or AWS EMR. Solid experience of both batch and streaming data pipelines
Strong software engineering background, with solid practices in CI/CD, automated testing, and version control
Advanced proficiency in SQL and database design, with a strong focus on performance optimisation and data modelling
Proven track record in infrastructure ownership, including deployment, system administration, monitoring, and operations (with a DevOps mindset)
Strong experience in coding with Python. Good experience with Scala is a bonus.
Solid experience with Cloud Data Warehouse like Databricks, Snowflake or Big Query
Deep understanding of cloud technology, preferably AWS with a focus on Big Data technologies such as EMR, Athena, Glue, and S3, as well as experience with IAM, Cloudformation, CDK, Lambda, SNS, SQS, SSM
Extensive background in supporting BI, Analytics, Data Science, and AI/ML initiatives
With at least 3+ years of experience in leading and mentoring team members, contributing to their technical growth and fostering a collaborative team culture
Demonstrated ability to own and deliver end-to-end solutions using Agile methodologies —driving initiative planning, iterative solution design, and stakeholder engagement to ensure alignment and value delivery
Additional Information

Permanent Perks

Support of flexible working, including a mix of office and work from home days depending on your role.
Paid and unpaid leave benefits including Personal Flexi Days and Volunteer Days, as well as the opportunity to purchase additional leave

SEEK is committed to operating sustainably and is preparing for the impacts of climate change and the transition to a low-carbon future, and is working to minimise its environmental impacts which includes a long-term emissions reduction target of net zero by FY2050

Job Title: Senior Software Engineer - AI Powered Engineering
Ad Text:
Senior Software Engineer - AI Powered Engineering




**Sydney OR Melbourne location**




You are passionate about AI and working to deliver better outcomes for CBA’s people and customers! 

We are leading the world in AI ambition within Australia’s largest bank and fintech! 

Together, we will engineer the future of banking with innovative Gen AI solutions! 




Your business  

The CIO for Technology team ensures that CommBank has a world-class engineering capability and is at the forefront of technology, using innovative and emerging technology to help our customers and support our Group Strategy. 

 We work hard to ensure that best practice, whether inside CommBank or outside in the broader technology ecosystem, is discovered, sheltered, nurtured, and spread to wherever else it can drive the most benefit for the Group and our customers. 

 We are actively involved in the technology community, contributing to education programs, innovation, research, and partnerships that will set Australia up for success as the economy transitions to a more digital future. 




Do work that matters 

 
Join our AI Powered Engineering function within the CIO for Technology portfolio. We are a very new, high-energy team with a startup like dynamic inside the Bank, partnering with our global engineering community to embed AI-assisted tools and capabilities that measurably improve developer experience, delivery velocity, and software quality. 




About the team 

 
We operate at the intersection of platform engineering, developer productivity, and applied AI. As a newly formed squad, we move fast, experiment responsibly, and ship pragmatic, reusable capabilities that fit enterprise standards. You’ll help shape our technical direction, culture, and ways of working from the ground up. 




What you’ll do  

Collaborate on complex technical problems from discovery through implementation, delivering high quality, maintainable solutions. 

Break down requirements into actionable engineering tasks; create clarity for delivery squads and stakeholders. 

Run hands-on experiments with emerging AI/ML and GenAI tooling; design evaluation frameworks, measure outcomes, and provide evidence-based recommendations. 

Build resilient, reusable components, SDKs, and service integrations that slot into pipelines, IDEs, and developer platforms. 

Contribute to architectural discussions; propose improvements and role model engineering standards and best practices. 

Maintain high quality codebases via active code reviews, robust testing, and clear documentation for knowledge sharing. 

Work cross functionally to align roadmaps, manage dependencies, and land changes with minimal disruption. 

Mentor junior engineers and uplift AI literacy across squads; contribute to communities of practice. 




What you bring  

Extensive experience in designing and implementing scalable, maintainable, and reliable software systems. 

Proficiency in one or more languages such as Python, TypeScript/Node.js, or C#, and experience building microservices on AWS and/or Azure. 

Architectures: Microservices, event driven patterns, REST/gRPC 

Cloud: AWS or Azure or GCP (e.g., Lambda/Functions, Containers/ECS/AKS, S3/Blob, API Gateway, Step Functions/Logic Apps) 

Data: SQL, data pipelines, observability/telemetry for engineering productivity and quality metrics 

DevSecOps: GitHub/GitLab/Azure DevOps, Actions/Pipelines, Terraform (IaC), SAST/DAST/SCA, secrets management 

Strong technical influence: ability to review designs and code, set quality bars, and collaborate with stakeholders to solve business critical problems. 

A growth mindset and bias toward iterative experimentation—from idea to prototype to pilot to product—with clear success metrics. 

Proficiency in agile delivery (Scrum/Kanban) and tooling such as Jira and Confluence. 

Good to have: Exposure to AI tools such as Roo Code, Claude or any other CLIs




If this sounds like you, apply today!

Company:

Company Perks

Job Summary
Analyse and identify opportunities within Maintenance to deliver improved reliability and asset performance. Work in a manufacturing environment collaborating with Maintenance, Production, Engineering, Calibration, PFT, and external service teams.
This position is an initial 6 month fixed term contract.

Key Responsibilities
Analyse downtime data to identify trends and patterns.
Optimise Preventative Maintenance (PM) plans in consultation with maintenance team members.
Modify and upload plant manuals, including PM plans.
Work closely with maintenance technicians to gain feedback from unplanned stoppages and PM shortcomings.
Collaborate with the Maintenance Planner to make spare parts recommendations, including criticality assessments and stock rationale.
Create weekly and monthly Maintenance and Reliability KPIs and deliver performance metric updates.
Manage the portfolio of assets to identify aging equipment and develop business cases for replacements, including obsolescence and write-offs.
Continuously review and update asset/equipment criticality.
Lead root cause investigations into significant unplanned events and ensure actions are completed to prevent recurrence.
Drive continuous improvement of CMMS data accuracy, including asset details, work frequency, and required parts and consumables.
Liaise effectively with production regarding maintenance-related issues.
Apply creative thinking, tenacity, and dedication to improve asset performance and operational productivity.
Position Specific Skills & Challenges:
Prior experience as a Reliability or Process Engineer.
Experience with Oracle EAM or other CMMS systems.
High attention to detail.
Intermediate to advanced skills in Microsoft Office Suite.
Excellent communication skills and the ability to build relationships with internal and external stakeholders.

Qualifications & Experience:
Engineering degree in Mechatronics, Mechanical, Electrical, or Chemical disciplines.
Trade qualifications in Mechanical or Electrical fields with relevant experience may be considered in lieu of a degree.
Preferred:
Minimum 2 years’ experience as a Manufacturing or Reliability Engineer.
Experience with CMMS.

About Us:

At Lockheed Martin Australia, we believe that when people are empowered, inspired, and supported, they can achieve extraordinary things. Systems Engineer Opportunities – Defence and Advanced Technology Programs

We’re expanding our engineering team and have new Systems Engineer openings across a range of advanced Defence and technology programs.

As a Systems Engineer, you’ll help shape next-generation capability by applying Model-Based Engineering (MBE) to design, develop and integrate complex systems. You’ll work closely with specialists, partner organisations and cross-functional teams to deliver solutions that strengthen Australia’s Defence and national security outcomes.

About the Role:

In this role, you will:

Analyse and transform system and sub-system requirements into detailed designs within an MBE environment.

Define and manage system interfaces, ensuring full traceability throughout the design lifecycle.

Conduct trade studies and optimise design solutions against performance, cost, and schedule considerations.

Produce and maintain technical artefacts — including design descriptions, requirements documents, and analysis reports.

Participate in design reviews and support project planning, stakeholder engagement, and engineering assurance activities.

Contribute to estimates, bids, and continuous improvement initiatives across programs.


About You:

You are a capable Systems Engineer who enjoys tackling complex technical problems and working in multidisciplinary teams. You’ll bring: 

Demonstrated experience across the systems engineering lifecycle, including requirements, design, integration, and verification.

Knowledge of MBSE approaches and tools such as MagicDraw, Rhapsody, Cameo or similar.

Experience working on complex systems, ideally within Defence or high-technology environments.

Strong analytical, modelling, and documentation skills.

A collaborative mindset with the ability to mentor or support junior engineers.


Why Join Us:

At Lockheed Martin Australia, you’ll work on programs that push the boundaries of innovation, engineering excellence and mission capability. Whether you’re passionate about systems design, integration, digital engineering or model-based development, you’ll have opportunities to learn, lead and grow.

Be part of something bigger — help shape the future of Defence systems and advanced technology.

Apply now for one of our Systems Engineer opportunities.


How we reward and support you: 

When you join Lockheed Martin, you work on projects you won’t experience anywhere else.

We offer you a range of benefits built to suit you, no matter what stage of life you are in. 

Flexible work & Hybrid work options

Access to our online discounts program offering immediate discounts or cashback

A variety of leave options including Purchase Leave to support you and your family  

Additional benefits such as Annual Flu Vaccinations, Novated Leasing and Fitness Programs


Special Requirements:

Applicants must be eligible to obtain and maintain an Australian Defence Security Clearance and employment may be contingent on the provision of further personal information including citizenship to ensure compliance with international export control legislation and regulations.

A Veteran-friendly Workplace:

Veterans are encouraged to apply. We highly value the unique skills and experiences that veterans and transitioning service members can contribute to our team. We are proud to be recognised as a Veteran Friendly Employer by the Australian Government.

Equal Opportunity Statement:

Lockheed Martin Australia supports Equal Employment Opportunity and values diversity in the workplace by creating a place of employment that is, free of unlawful discrimination and is harassment free, fair, ethical, inclusive, and values the contribution of all its employees. Job Title: Staff Software Engineer - AI Powered Engineering
Ad Text:
Staff Software Engineer - AI Powered Engineering 

**Sydney or Melbourne locations**

You are passionate about AI and working to deliver better outcomes  

We are leading the world in AI ambition within Australia’s largest bank and fintech! 

Together, we will engineer the future of banking with innovative Gen AI solutions! 




Your business  

The CIO for Technology team ensures that CommBank has a world-class engineering capability and is at the forefront of technology, using innovative and emerging technology to help our customers and support our Group Strategy. 

We work hard to ensure that best practice, whether inside CommBank or outside in the broader technology ecosystem, is discovered, sheltered, nurtured, and spread to wherever else it can drive the most benefit for the Group and our customers. 

We are actively involved in the technology community, contributing to education programs, innovation, research, and partnerships that will set Australia up for success as the economy transitions to a more digital future. 




Do work that matters  

Join our AI Powered Engineering function within the CIO for Technology portfolio. Our mandate is clear: partner with CommBank’s global engineering community to responsibly embed AI-assisted tools and capabilities that materially lift developer experience, delivery velocity, and software quality across the bank. 




About the team  

We’re a hands-on, product-minded engineering group operating at the intersection of platform engineering, developer productivity, and applied AI. We experiment, validate, and scale AI-enabled capabilities that integrate into existing engineering workflows—always grounded in safety, reliability, and measurable impact. 




What you’ll do 

Collaborate on complex technical problems from discovery to implementation, ensuring high-quality engineering outcomes. 

Translate business and engineering requirements into clear, actionable designs; break down work and create clarity for delivery squads. 

Experiment with emerging AI/ML and GenAI tooling; run fit-for-purpose evaluations and provide grounded recommendations from real-world testing. 

Deliver resilient, reusable components and services that integrate into other teams’ products and pipelines. 

Contribute to architecture discussions; propose improvements and role-model engineering standards and best practices. 

Maintain high-quality codebases through active code reviews and documentation that scales knowledge across the community. 

Work cross-functionally to align roadmaps, manage dependencies, and land change with minimal disruption. 

Provide technical guidance and mentorship to engineers and squad members, uplifting engineering craft and AI literacy. 

What you bring 

Extensive experience designing and implementing scalable, maintainable, and reliable software systems. 

Proficiency in one or more languages such as Python, TypeScript, or C#, and experience building microservices on public cloud (AWS and/or Azure). 

Architectures: Microservices, event-driven patterns, REST/gRPC 

Cloud: AWS or Azure or GCP (e.g., Lambda/Functions, ECS/AKS, S3/Blob, API Gateway, Step Functions/Logic Apps) 

Data: SQL, data pipelines, observability/telemetry for engineering productivity metrics 

DevSecOps: GitHub/GitLab/Azure DevOps, Actions/Pipelines, IaC (Terraform), SAST/DAST/SCA, secrets management 

Strong technical leadership and stakeholder management skills: ability to set technical direction, review designs and code, and influence stakeholders to solve business‑critical problems. 

Growth mindset with a bias toward iterative experimentation—from idea to prototype to pilot to product—with a clear view of success metrics. 

Desirable: Experience with API tools such as RooCode or Claude or any other CLIs.

Desirable: Familiarity with cybersecurity frameworks (e.g., NIST) to support secure engineering practices.




If this sounds like you, apply today! 




We support flexibility with a hybrid approach—at least half your time each month connecting in office—plus options such as adjusted start/finish times, part‑time, and job share.

ITIL Foundation

Ad Text:

You’ll play a pivotal role in guiding the implementation of Azure AI services, Databricks, and modern MLOps practices to support high-impact use cases across the business. Day to day:

Evaluate and experiment with emerging LLMs, embeddings, and generative AI capabilities, and lead their application in production use cases

Deep experience with Databricks, Spark, Delta Lake, and MLflow

Azure Machine Learning

Excellent stakeholder engagement skills – ability to translate business needs into AI solutions with measurable outcomes
Familiarity with data governance, privacy (e.g. GDPR), and responsible AI frameworks

Position Description:


Recognised as one of the world’s largest IT and business consulting firms, CGI has offices across Australia, supporting local public and private sector clients to solve real business problems.

We are looking to hire a Data Modeller who will focus on translating complex business requirements into clear, scalable, conceptual, logical, and physical data models that support analytics, reporting, and operational needs. Working closely with data engineers, analysts, and business stakeholders, the Data Modeller ensures that data is well-organized, standardized, and aligned with governance and quality frameworks to enable efficient data-driven decision-making across the organization.

Flexible work is available including hybrid work from client’s site at Port Melbourne.

Your future duties and responsibilities:


• Contribute to the design, development, and continuous refinement of conceptual, logical, and physical data models within the Data Transformation team.
• Create and maintain SQL DDL scripts, along with detailed mapping and ETL documentation, to support Data Engineers in constructing and loading data models.
• When required, carry out reverse engineering of existing data models from databases or SQL code to ensure alignment with current architecture and standards.
• Develop and update business documentation, including process maps, taxonomies, and ontology diagrams, to provide clarity and traceability of data flows.
• Maintain a strong emphasis on conceptual and business data modelling, ensuring that structures align with organisational objectives.
• Interpret and translate business requirements into scalable data models that support long-term analytical and operational needs.
• Assist in managing and maintaining controlled vocabularies and the corporate data catalogue to promote consistency and reuse of data assets.
• Participate in modelling workshops and collaborative sessions with other Data Modellers to align on best practices and design approaches.
• Adhere to existing Data Quality and Data Governance frameworks, contributing to their ongoing enhancement and ensuring compliance with modelling standards.
• Build and maintain effective working relationships with subject matter experts and business stakeholders across the organisation.
• Keep stakeholders and senior management informed of prioritisation decisions, project progress, and delivery timelines, managing expectations clearly and proactively.

Required qualifications to be successful in this role:


• Sound understanding of data modelling methodologies, including Kimball, Inmon, Top-down/Bottom-up, Relational and Dimensional Modelling, Data Warehousing, and 3NF approaches.
• Ability to think conceptually and apply modelling techniques such as generalisation, subtyping, and super-typing to create efficient and flexible models.
• Skilled in producing Entity Relationship Diagrams (ERDs) using a range of notations, such as Crow’s Foot and UML.
• Strong technical understanding of databases, ETL/ELT pipelines, and programming languages (typically SQL), with the ability to connect these technologies to data modelling practices. (This is a hands-on role involving active work with data.)
• Solid comprehension of business processes, with the ability to capture requirements accurately and translate them into effective technical designs.
• Confident communicator, capable of engaging in technical discussions with both technical and non-technical audiences across all organisational levels.
• Experience with cloud-based data technologies would be advantageous, particularly within the Microsoft Azure ecosystem, including:
o Azure Data Lake
o Azure Data Factory
o Azure Databricks (SQL and Python)
o Azure SQL Server
o Azure DevOps / Git

Skills:

Azure Data Factory
Azure Data Lake
Azure DevOps
Python
